full_text = "**UNITED STATES ENVIRONMENTAL PROTECTION AGENCY**\n**Region 5 - Water Division**\n\n**INSPECTION REPORT**\n**Facility Inspection No.:** 2024-R5-WTR-1094\n**Inspection Date:** July 22-23, 2024\n**Report Issued:** August 15, 2024\n**Lead Inspector:** Janet Kowalski, PE (Environmental Engineer)\n\n**Facility Information:**\nFacility Name: [REDACTED - FOIA Exemption 4: Confidential Business Information]\nPhysical Address: [REDACTED], River County, Illinois\nNPDES Permit No.: IL-[REDACTED]\nReceiving Water Body: [REDACTED] Wetland Complex (Class II Waters)\n\n**FINDING 1: Unpermitted Discharge Point**\n**Severity: MAJOR VIOLATION**\n\nInspectors identified an undocumented discharge pipe (designated as \"Outfall 004\") located on the eastern boundary of the facility. This pipe was not listed in the current NPDES permit.\n\nFlow rate estimated at [REDACTED] gallons per day. Discharge observed entering [REDACTED] wetland approximately 200 meters downstream.\n\n**Facility Response:**\nEnvironmental Compliance Officer M. Patel stated that Outfall 004 was a \"stormwater overflow\" and not subject to permit requirements. However, inspectors noted continuous flow during dry weather conditions, inconsistent with stormwater designation.\n\n**FINDING 2: Effluent Limit Exceedances**\n**Severity: MAJOR VIOLATION**\n\nLaboratory analysis of samples collected from Outfall 004 revealed the following parameter exceedances:\n\n| Parameter | Detected | Permit Limit | Exceedance |\n|-----------|----------|--------------|------------|\n| Total Chromium | [REDACTED] mg/L | [REDACTED] mg/L | [REDACTED]% |\n| Lead | [REDACTED] mg/L | [REDACTED] mg/L | [REDACTED]% |\n| pH | [REDACTED] | 6.0-9.0 | Outside Range |\n\n**Note:** Specific concentration values redacted pursuant to FOIA Exemption 4 (confidential business information).\n\n**FINDING 3: Falsified Discharge Monitoring Reports**\n**Severity: MAJOR VIOLATION**\n\nReview of DMRs for January-June 2024 showed no reported discharges from Outfall 004. Facility records indicated that monitoring data for this outfall was either not collected or not reported.\n\n**Facility Response:**\n[REDACTED - Exemption 7(A): Ongoing enforcement investigation]\n\n**FINDING 4: Receiving Water Impacts**\n**Severity: SIGNIFICANT**\n\nSampling of [REDACTED] wetland sediment and surface water revealed:\n- Elevated heavy metal concentrations in sediment (see attached Table 3)\n- [REDACTED - Exemption 5: Pre-decisional agency memo]\n- Presence of biomarkers indicating chronic toxic stress in aquatic organisms\n\n**Enforcement Recommendations:**\n\nOriginal Recommendation (July 25, 2024):\n[REDACTED - Exemption 7(A): Would interfere with ongoing enforcement proceedings]\n\nRevised Recommendation (August 10, 2024):\nEPA recommends that [REDACTED] enter into a voluntary compliance agreement to:\n1. Conduct comprehensive site assessment within 180 days\n2. Submit corrective action plan within 270 days\n3. Implement remediation measures on a timeline to be negotiated with Region 5\n\nCivil Penalty Assessment:\n[REDACTED - Exemption 7(A)]\n\n[STAMP:] PUBLIC VERSION - CONFIDENTIAL BUSINESS INFORMATION REMOVED"
